"script": "There's a jellyfish that, when it's about to die, simply grows young again. It's barely bigger than a fingernail, but it carries one of nature's strangest tricks. When it's injured, starving, or old, it doesn't give up. Instead, its body collapses into a blob and sinks to the seafloor. And then its cells transform, rewinding it back into its baby stage, like a butterfly turning back into a caterpillar. From there, it grows up all over again. In theory, it can repeat this cycle forever, which is why scientists call it the immortal jellyfish.",
